  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Somalia: Strengthening Linkages between Formal Justice System and Traditional Dispute Resolution System to Improve Access to Justice</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">1. To enhance the capacity of the Ministry of Justice and Constitutional Affairs and NGOs to engage with TDR mechanisms. 2. To strengthen the accessibility and effectiveness of the justice system by improving knowledge of the traditional dispute resolution system and strengthening linkages between it and the formal justice system. 3. To strengthen the compatibility of customary systems with international and national law. 4. To promote stability in Somalia through the social reintegration of low-risk ex-fighters using TDR processes.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The MoJC TDR Unit, Somali Justice Sector and Somali citizens</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project aimed to support the establishment, and build the capacity of, the Traditional Dispute Resolution (TDR) Unit within the Ministry of Justice, Religion, Constitutional and Reconciliation Affairs; undertake a pilot project in conjunction with local NGOs to increase knowledge about the institutions, laws and practices of TDR mechanisms and the functioning of the Elders&#x2019; Committees; and increase accountability of the decisions of the Elders&#x2019; Committees with regard to compliance with the Provisional Constitution and international human rights standards.</narrative>
  </description>
